Catenal position: On nearly flat plateau at the top of very shallow wide wet valley with water in parts.


Termite mounds: 14
	Counted by John during scanning

Time since last fire: Maybe last year, judging by the fresh looking charcoal on some of the smaller trees.

Animals: Palankas, Olongo 

Farming in last 30 years: No

Resource extraction: No

General notes: 
	This is definitely more like a Baikea Baphia woodland, though unlike the thick shrubby stuff seen in Plot 4, big Baikea trees and a few smaller baphia coppice trees. Long grass, low stem density, very nice to work in. Slightly more undergrowth than Plot 9, some spiky shrubs and longer grass. Makes me think it hasn't burned for longer, or doesn't burn as often.
